  "prompt": "Does a user always need to keep the data \u2018ON\u2019 for outgoing/incoming calls on Jio network?",
  "response": "On the Jio network in India, users do not need to keep mobile data \"ON\" for making or receiving voice calls. Jio primarily uses Voice over LTE (VoLTE) technology, which allows voice calls to be made over the LTE network. This means that you can make and receive calls without needing to have mobile data enabled.\n\nHowever, if you want to use certain features that require internet connectivity, such as Jio's video calling service or any other app that uses data for communication, then you would need to have mobile data turned on. But for standard voice calls, it is not necessary to keep data on.",
